{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Being a young boy, I was just under the opening, which was quite helpful because as the train went, being a boy, I pulled myself up, and I could look out.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I used to tell the people, because everybody was very squashed there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So a grownup could hardly have made himself room to move his arms and his legs to, to pull himself up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I as a child could in a second pull myself up and look out and could hold myself inside, or somebody help me to hold me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now, when these deportations happened, my uncle and the other few people who were arrested by the gestapo as soon as they entered the town, were brought directly to the train, and they were put on the same train.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The story is that the Judenrat from Budapest organized a so-called Palestina Transport.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "People who were of Zionist connection and background were supposed to have been seven to 10 families per large ghetto taken out off the deportation trains, of the various provincial centers where the deportations went on, and taken to Budapest into a ghetto where they were not to be deported.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My uncle, Dr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Bela Weiler, had a very close Zionist association.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I think he was on the first Hungarian Zionist Conference.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And he was near enough in contemporary, or just a little bit younger than Herzl.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And Herzl, as you know, was Vienna-Budapest origin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And when he was taken to the train-- it's very unfortunate, but when it comes to important things, people, I can't say really anything terrible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But its, it's very hard on the people who it happened to that lists of the people which were sent out from Budapest have been changed by the people who got hold of it.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
